# DAG Node Implementation Rules

## Purpose
Enforce a single, standard way to implement DAG nodes so validation and execution behavior stays consistent across all node packages.

## Non-Negotiable Rules
- Every new node definition class in `packages/dag-nodes/**/src/index.ts` MUST extend `AbstractNodeDefinition`.
- Node config validation MUST be handled through `configSchemaDefinition` + base-class runtime parse flow.
- Node logic MUST use typed `config` from `estimateCostWithConfig(...)` and `executeWithConfig(...)`.
- Do not read `context.nodeDefinition.config.*` directly inside node execution paths.
- List-binary inputs MUST be validated with `NodeIoAccessor.requireInputBinaryList(...)`.
- Do not manually read list-handle keys like `images[0]`, `images[1]` in node code.
- Single binary inputs MUST use `NodeIoAccessor.requireInputBinary(...)`.
- String/array input checks MUST use `NodeIoAccessor` helpers (`requireInputString`, `requireInputArray`, etc.).
- Cost computation MUST be implemented via `estimateCostWithConfig(...)` override in node definition classes.
- Do not implement ad-hoc handler classes that bypass the abstract node lifecycle.

## Validation Ownership
- `configSchemaDefinition` owns config shape and cross-field constraints.
- `AbstractNodeDefinition` owns runtime config parse and error mapping.
- `NodeIoAccessor` owns payload type guards and list/input utility validation.
- Node implementations own only feature/business rules and provider/runtime orchestration.

## Duplication Policy
- If the same validation pattern appears in two or more nodes, move it to `dag-core` helpers.
- Do not copy-paste `typeof`/trim/minItems validation blocks across node files when an accessor/helper can own it.

## Error Contract
- Validation failures must use `DAG_VALIDATION_*` codes.
- Execution/provider failures must use `DAG_TASK_EXECUTION_*` codes.
- Keep failure categories and retryability aligned with existing DAG error conventions.

## Build Requirement
- After any change in `packages/dag-core/src/` or `packages/dag-nodes/*/src/`, run package builds before finishing work.

